Company Overview of Stewart Capital Mutual Funds - Stewart Capital Mid Cap Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
As of November 18, 2016, Stewart Capital Mutual Funds - Stewart Capital Mid Cap Fund has gone out of business. Stewart Capital Mutual Funds - Stewart Capital Mid Cap Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Stewart Capital Advisors, LLC. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in value stocks of mid cap companies with market capitalization within the range of the Russell MidCap Value Index. It employs fundamental analysis by focusing on factors like strong management teams, favorable demographics, high barriers to entry, high returns on invested...
As of November 18, 2016, Stewart Capital Mutual Funds - Stewart Capital Mid Cap Fund has gone out of business. Stewart Capital Mutual Funds - Stewart Capital Mid Cap Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Stewart Capital Advisors, LLC. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in value stocks of mid cap companies with market capitalization within the range of the Russell MidCap Value Index. It employs fundamental analysis by focusing on factors like strong management teams, favorable demographics, high barriers to entry, high returns on invested capital, and long-term trends to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the S&P 400 Midcap Index and the Russell MidCap Value Index. Stewart Capital Mutual Funds - Stewart Capital Mid Cap Fund was formed on December 29, 2006 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


